To make a component using Framer Motion re-render when the data it is using changes, you can use the useEffect hook in React. The useEffect hook allows you to specify a function that should be run when a specific variable changes.Here is an example of how you might use the useEffect hook to make a Framer Motion component re-render when the data it is using changes:Copy codeimport { useEffect } from 'react';
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';
import useSWR from 'swr';

function MyComponent() {
  // Use the SWR hook to fetch data from an API endpoint
  const { data } = useSWR('/api/my-data');

  // Use the useEffect hook to re-render the component when the data changes
  useEffect(() => {
    // The component will re-render every time the data changes
  }, [data]);

  return (
    <motion.div
      // Use the data to animate the component
      animate={{ x: data }}
    />
  );
}
In this example, the useEffect hook is being used to specify that the MyComponent should re-render whenever the data variable changes. This means that the component will re-render whenever the data it is using changes, which will cause the Framer Motion animation to update.I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.

